The paper deals with the analysis of auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic game theory (cs.EC). The use of submodular and subadditive valuations suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of combinatorial optimization (cs.DS). The paper also presents a new proof technique, which may be of interest to researchers in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
